  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) obligations\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Creating mechanisms for asset seizure and forfeiture\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must monitor transactions\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n- Implementing internal control systems\n- Regular risk assessments\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- Asset freezing and confiscation\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigative efforts\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
